{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839963623,"sessionID":"ses_287b0e365ffeqtLyxw9eoxzISj","part":{"id":"prt_d784f59a7001o1J6SNgABvx9Nq","messageID":"msg_d784f4f92001okTWxmKNYR9gCY","sessionID":"ses_287b0e365ffeqtLyxw9eoxzISj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a1e2e34511bc4c6895b329b6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage code interpreter configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing isolated kernel environments for AI agent code execution.\n6: \n7: The `CodeInterpreter` resource represents a configurable code execution environment with support for:\n8: - Multiple kernel languages (Python, R, Julia, etc.)\n9: - Session management and lifecycle\n10: - Security policies (package allowlists, operation restrictions)\n11: - Resource quotas (CPU, memory per session)\n12: - Status tracking (phase, conditions, active sessions)\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n17: **API Group:** `codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n18: **Kind:** `CodeInterpreter` (namespaced)  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n24:    - `CodeInterpreter` - main resource struct\n25:    - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - desired state specification\n26:    - `CodeInterpreterStatus` - observed state status\n27:    - `KernelSpec` - kernel configuration (language, image, resources)\n28:    - `SessionConfig` - session timeout and limits\n29:    - `SecurityPolicy` - package allowlists and operation restrictions\n30:    - `CodeInterpreterPhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n31:    - `CodeInterpreterCondition` - status conditions\n32: \n33: 2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n34:    - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n35:    - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n36:    - `AddToScheme` function\n37:    - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n38: \n39: 3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`)\n40:    - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n41:    - Subresources: `/status`\n42:    - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n43:    - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n44: \n45: 4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n46:    - `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` - default values\n47:    - `ValidateCodeInterpreter` - spec validation rules\n48:    - `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n49: \n50: 5. **Utility Functions**\n51:    - Phase transition helpers\n52:    - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n53:    - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n54: \n55: ### Out of Scope\n56: \n57: - Controller implementation (deferred to AR-003)\n58: - Kernel image building and management (infrastructure task)\n59: - Session WebSocket proxying (deferred to router component)\n60: - Python SDK bindings (Python SDK task)\n61: \n62: ## Impact Analysis\n63: \n64: ### Dependencies\n65: \n66: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n67: |------------|------|--------|\n68: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n69: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, SecurityContext, EnvVar |\n70: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n71: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n72: \n73: ### Downstream Consumers\n74: \n75: 1. **Controller (AR-003)**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` resources, reconciles to create kernel pods\n76: 2. **AgentRuntime (AR-001)**: References `CodeInterpreter` for agent code execution capability\n77: 3. **Router**: Manages WebSocket connections to active interpreter sessions\n78: 4. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing CodeInterpreter resources\n79: 5. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube interpreter create/get/list/delete` commands\n80: 6. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n81: \n82: ### Breaking Changes\n83: \n84: None - this is the initial definition of the API.\n85: \n86: ### Migration Path\n87: \n88: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n89: - Conversion webhook implementation\n90: - Storage version bumps\n91: - Helm chart upgrade hooks\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 1: Embed CodeInterpreter config in AgentRuntime\n96: \n97: **Approach:** Include code interpreter configuration as a nested field within `AgentRuntime` spec.\n98: \n99: **Pros:**\n100: - Single resource to manage\n101: - Simpler deployment model\n102: - No additional CRD overhead\n103: \n104: **Cons:**\n105: - Couples agent lifecycle with interpreter lifecycle\n106: - Cannot share interpreters across agents\n107: - Harder to scale interpreters independently\n108: - Limits multi-language support per agent\n109: \n110: **Decision:** Rejected. Separating concerns allows interpreters to be managed, scaled, and versioned independently. Multiple agents can reference the same interpreter, and agents can switch interpreters without recreation.\n111: \n112: ### Alternative 2: Use Jupyter kernel gateway directly\n113: \n114: **Approach:** Deploy Jupyter Kernel Gateway as a standard Deployment and manage kernels via REST API.\n115: \n116: **Pros:**\n117: - Leverages existing Jupyter ecosystem\n118: - Mature kernel management\n119: - Built-in WebSocket support\n120: \n121: **Cons:**\n122: - No Kubernetes-native resource model\n123: - Custom integration required for lifecycle management\n124: - Harder to enforce cluster-wide policies\n125: - No status reporting to Kubernetes API\n126: \n127: **Decision:** Partially adopted. CodeInterpreter CRD represents the desired state; controller will create/manage Jupyter Kernel Gateway deployments based on CRD spec. This combines K8s-native abstraction with proven kernel technology.\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 3: One CodeInterpreter per language\n130: \n131: **Approach:** Create separate CRDs for PythonInterpreter, RInterpreter, JuliaInterpreter, etc.\n132: \n133: **Pros:**\n134: - Language-specific validation rules\n135: - Clear separation of concerns\n136: - Simpler schemas per CRD\n137: \n138: **Cons:**\n139: - CRD proliferation\n140: - Duplicate code across CRDs\n141: - Harder to support polyglot agents\n142: - More complex client code\n143: \n144: **Decision:** Rejected. Single `CodeInterpreter` CRD with `KernelSpec.language` field provides flexibility while maintaining simplicity. Validation rules can branch on language field.\n145: \n146: ## Implementation Plan\n147: \n148: 1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n149:    - `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n150:    - `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/register.go` (group registration)\n151: \n152: 2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n153:    - Core structs with JSON tags\n154:    - Phase enum and conditions\n155:    - KernelSpec and SecurityPolicy\n156: \n157: 3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n158:    - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n159:    - SchemeBuilder wiring\n160: \n161: 4. **Add defaults and validation**\n162:    - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter\n163:    - `validation.go`: ValidateCodeInterpreter\n164: \n165: 5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n166:    - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n167:    - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n168: \n169: 6. **Generate client code**\n170:    - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n171:    - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n172: \n173: 7. **Write unit tests**\n174:    - Type round-trip serialization\n175:    - Defaulting behavior\n176:    - Validation rules\n177: \n178: ## Success Criteria\n179: \n180: - [ ] `CodeInterpreter` CRD installs via Helm chart\n181: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f codeinterpreter.yaml` succeeds\n182: - [ ] `kubectl get codeinterpreter` shows custom columns\n183: - [ ] Go client can create/get/update CodeInterpreter\n184: - [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n185: - [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n186: - [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n187: \n188: ## References\n189: \n190: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n191: - [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n192: - [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n193: - Jupyter Kernel Gateway: https://jupyter-kernel-gateway.readthedocs.io/\n194: - Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage code interpreter configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing isolated kernel environments for AI agent code execution.\n\nThe `CodeInterpreter` resource represents a configurable code execution environment with support for:\n- Multiple kernel languages (Python, R, Julia, etc.)\n- Session management and lifecycle\n- Security policies (package allowlists, operation restrictions)\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory per session)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, active sessions)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `CodeInterpreter` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839963607,"end":1775839963622}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839963625,"sessionID":"ses_287b0e365ffeqtLyxw9eoxzISj","part":{"id":"prt_d784f5f23001KSk0qReAnKqepI","messageID":"msg_d784f4f92001okTWxmKNYR9gCY","sessionID":"ses_287b0e365ffeqtLyxw9eoxzISj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_80502f9e4a6748b8aca2b4e4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/register.go` - register API group\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n20: \n21: - [ ] **2.1** Define `CodeInterpreterPhase` enum (Pending, Running, Failed, Terminating)\n22: - [ ] **2.2** Define `CodeInterpreterCondition` struct (type, status, reason, message, lastTransitionTime)\n23: - [ ] **2.3** Define `KernelSpec` struct (language, image, resources)\n24: - [ ] **2.4** Define `SessionConfig` struct (timeout, idleTimeout, maxSessions)\n25: - [ ] **2.5** Define `SecurityPolicy` struct (allowedPackages, blockedOperations, networkAccess)\n26: - [ ] **2.6** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct (kernel, session, security, resources)\n27: - [ ] **2.7** Define `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct (phase, conditions, activeSessions, startTime, lastTransitionTime)\n28: - [ ] **2.8** Define `CodeInterpreter` struct (TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, Status)\n29: - [ ] **2.9** Define `CodeInterpreterList` struct (TypeMeta, ListMeta, Items)\n30: - [ ] **2.10** Add JSON tags (camelCase) and protobuf tags to all types\n31: - [ ] **2.11** Implement `runtime.Object` interface for CodeInterpreter and CodeInterpreterList\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Phase 3: Defaults & Validation\n36: \n37: - [ ] **3.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/defaults.go`\n38: - [ ] **3.2** Implement `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` - set default phase to Pending, default kernel settings\n39: - [ ] **3.3** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/validation.go`\n40: - [ ] **3.4** Implement `ValidateCodeInterpreter` - validate spec fields (kernel language, resource values, security policies)\n41: - [ ] **3.5** Implement `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate` - validate status transitions and field immutability\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Phase 4: CRD Manifest Generation\n46: \n47: - [ ] **4.1** Add `+genclient` and `+k8s:deepcopy-gen` markers to type definitions\n48: - [ ] **4.2** Add `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers\n49: - [ ] **4.3** Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers for kubectl output (NAME, PHASE, KERNEL, AGE)\n50: - [ ] **4.4** Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen) to generate CRD YAML\n51: - [ ] **4.5** Verify generated manifest at `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n52: - [ ] **4.6** Validate OpenAPI v3 schema in generated CRD\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## Phase 5: Client Code Generation\n57: \n58: - [ ] **5.1** Update `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` if needed\n59: - [ ] **5.2** Update `hack/update-codegen.sh` with API group info\n60: - [ ] **5.3** Run `make gen-client` to generate clientset, listers, informers\n61: - [ ] **5.4** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/clientset/versioned/`\n62: - [ ] **5.5** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/listers/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n63: - [ ] **5.6** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/informers/externalversions/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## Phase 6: Unit Tests\n68: \n69: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n70: - [ ] **6.2** Test type round-trip serialization (Go → JSON → Go)\n71: - [ ] **6.3** Test `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` behavior\n72: - [ ] **6.4** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/validation_test.go`\n73: - [ ] **6.5** Test valid CodeInterpreter specs pass validation\n74: - [ ] **6.6** Test invalid specs fail validation (unsupported languages, negative resources)\n75: - [ ] **6.7** Test status update validation (phase transitions, immutable fields)\n76: - [ ] **6.8** Test `AddToScheme` registration works correctly\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Phase 7: Integration & Verification\n81: \n82: - [ ] **7.1** Run `make test` - all unit tests pass\n83: - [ ] **7.2** Run `make verify` - code generation is up to date\n84: - [ ] **7.3** Apply CRD to test cluster: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n85: - [ ] **7.4** Verify `kubectl get codeinterpreter` shows custom columns\n86: - [ ] **7.5** Create sample CodeInterpreter YAML in `examples/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n87: - [ ] **7.6** Apply sample and verify resource is created\n88: - [ ] **7.7** Verify Go client can create/get/update CodeInterpreter resources\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## Verification Checklist\n93: \n94: - [ ] All Go code compiles without errors\n95: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/...` passes with ≥80% coverage\n96: - [ ] CRD manifest validates with `kubeval` or `kubectl --dry-run=server`\n97: - [ ] Generated client code is up to date (`git diff` shows no changes after `make gen-client`)\n98: - [ ] Example YAML applies successfully to test cluster\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Dependencies\n103: \n104: | Task | Depends On |\n105: |------|------------|\n106: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 |\n107: | Phase 3